# Whispers of Autumn

Amber leaves dance upon the breeze,
Whispering secrets of the changing year.
Summer's warmth begins to fade,
As autumn's palette draws near.

Crimson, gold, and burnished bronze,
Paint the landscape far and wide.
Nature's final burst of color,
Before winter's quiet tide.

The scent of earth and fallen fruit,
Mingles with the cooling air.
Harvest moon hangs full and bright,
Casting shadows everywhere.

Creatures bustle, storing food,
Preparing for the frost to come.
Birds in formation overhead,
Their southern journey just begun.

I wrap my scarf a little tighter,
As twilight falls so swift and soon.
Savoring these fleeting moments,
Knowing winter follows soon.

Yet in this gentle transformation,
There's beauty in the slow decay.
For in endings lie beginnings,
As night gives way to day.
